{"award_age":42.0,"bio_image":"full\/6e421fae983614a40563f68c1a3b38ea7103d332.jpg","category":"Chemistry","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1947-12-08T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/6\/68\/Thomas_Robert_Cech.jpg\/220px-Thomas_Robert_Cech.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_R._Cech","mini_bio":"<p><b>Thomas Robert Cech<\/b> (born December 8, 1947) is an American chemist who shared the 1989 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_prize\" title=\"Nobel prize\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Nobel prize<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chemistry\" title=\"Chemistry\">chemistry<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sidney_Altman\" title=\"Sidney Altman\">Sidney Altman<\/a>, for their discovery of the catalytic properties of RNA. Cech discovered that RNA could itself cut strands of RNA, which showed that life could have started as RNA.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_R._Cech#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He also studied <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Telomeres\" title=\"Telomeres\" class=\"mw-redirect\">telomeres<\/a>, and his lab discovered an enzyme, TERT (telomerase reverse transcriptase), which is part of the process of restoring telomeres after they are shortened during cell division.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_R._Cech#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> As president of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Howard_Hughes_Medical_Institute\" title=\"Howard Hughes Medical Institute\">Howard Hughes Medical Institute<\/a>, he promoted science education, and he teaches an undergraduate chemistry course at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Colorado\" title=\"University of Colorado\">University of Colorado<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Thomas R. Cech","place_of_birth":"Chicago ,  United States","place_of_death":null,"text":"Thomas R. Cech , Chemistry, 1989","year":1989.0}